About Cloud

Having access to resources using a network on demand. it is called as "cloud"

The resources can be - file, email, audio, video, software, hardware requests & processing etc.

Access these resources from a remote location.

	Ex - Gmail, Yahoo, Outlook, etc


					 Cloud - Types

Based on network types, there are four types of cloud -

Private Cloud
Public Cloud
Hybrid Cloud
Social / Community  Cloud
					Private Cloud

		* client/server - 1973 IBM, released to market in 1978

	   	* Accessing resources using a private network on demand is called as private cloud

		* Example : Project - Travel - to office - and work.
* Novel Networks - 1990

		* Dell(EMC) and IBM are leaders currently..

		1990 - VPN - "Virtual Private Network"

	To Access a private network of an organization using a public network is VPN.
	
						 Public cloud 

		* Accessing resources using Public network on demand --> public cloud

		* post internet evolution : 1994, (India 1996)

		internet - UN - 1987 - connecting all networks of world, 1992 - 1993  

		ICANN -: 1994  USA, Russia, European ( 1994, 1995 ) ( India - 1996 )

		* Accessing resources over public network (internet) on demand based 		  	it is called as "public cloud"

		* existence from 1996 ....

* Here, using these services we need to pay --? " PAY PER USE MODEL "

1. Charge based on usage
2. pay it after using resources (POST payment)
3. No deposit or investment

