***** Public cloud services: ( pay per use model )  ***** 

1. IAAS - infrastructure as a service
* client --> vendor ( AWS ) --> hardwares ;; 
* client will have to setup rest of things ( OS Setup , Application Setup, etc )

	--> AWS is a leader
	--> 2005, Microsoft was largest holder of Data centers, 2018 AWS Largest data centers holder, 6X (Report - GARNER)
	

2. PAAS - Platform as a service

* client --> will get from cloud vendor ( hardware + os )

* client will have to setup the application

	---> both AWS/azure are same page.


3. SAAS - Software as a service

client --> app (billing/hotels) --> cloud vendor (AWS)--> 'modelled applications'

	--> customize for u --> application --> use it. -->  Pay it

If SAAS was not there, alt.solution: { IT company, Hire developer, self }

	-- client zero maintainence -- pay for it.

--> *SALES FORCE is a leader, AWS, Oracle

	---> 1996, force.com --> infosys, IBM, --> technology SAAS

4. XAAS - "Everything as a service"

     --> service, whatever client asks - cloud provide - hardware, application, network, support, etc

	--> IBM is a leader

Other services -

** NAAS - Network  as a service
** DBAAS - Database as a service
** DAAS - Database as a service
** CAAS - Container as a Service
** FAAS - Fileserver as a service
** VAAS - VCS as a service    

