Introduction to EC2

EC2 - Elastic Cloud compute
if we create a computer online and access it from anywhere -- "online virtual server"
Ec2 - is all about creating an online virtual server, which can be accessed over the internet.
Ec2 - comes under free tier services but with some limitation

1. Choose AMI (Amazon Machine Image)  - select the OS
2. Choose Instance Type - Hardware ( CPU, RAM, STORAGE DISK, MOTHERBOARD TYPES)
3. Configure Instance -  .. simply .. next
4. Add Storage - Space needed for HDD disk
5. Add Tags - Names ur computers
6. Configure Security Group - setup of ports
7. Review - 

keypair(password)-file-download--> called as PEM File
Privacy Enhanced mail.

Ec2 - create -will two IP address: IPV4

	1. Private IP
	2. Public IP

-> to connect Ec2, we are supposed to use Public IP v4
--> Talk from one Ec2 to another Ec2 - use Private IP v4

What details u have about Ec2?

	- IP public v4
	- password ( pem file )
	- login ID 
	- App to connect - gitbash, putty


# ssh login_id@ipv4address -i <pemfile>

* When we are using putty, we need ppk file and not pem file.
* AWS --> download --> pem file --> puttygen converts pem into ppk

Site: https://www.chiark.greenend.org.uk/~sgtatham/putty/latest.html

* using ppk in putty, we need connect to AWS Ec2

** Process to convert pem into ppk file **

1. open puttygen
2. click on Load and browse to pem file
3. click on Save Private key

Note : Restart the computer..

              Connect EC2- Linux Instance using Putty

1. make sure we have ppk file ready

2. Open putty, put the userid@public_Ipv4_AWS_Ec2_instance

3. Then, expand "connection" then expand "SSH"

4. Now, select "AUTH", browse to ppk file.


